Health workers fill out documents before performing tests for COVID-19 coronavirus on other health workers at the screening and testing tents set up at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital in Johannesburg, on April 15, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 5,350 with the death toll increasing to 103. This is an increase of 354 cases from Tuesday. This is also the highest number of cases in a 24-hour cycle recorded to date. The total number of tests conducted to date is 197,127 of which 11,630 were done in the last 24 hours. Health Media Release 29.04.... by Travis Richards on Scribd 